			<div type="leaf">
				<p>
					<pb facs="#f021"/>
					<metamark change="metadata#StB" facs="#f021_z040" function="folio" n="20" place="top right margin" rend="no_caret">folio number 20</metamark>
				</p>
				<p>
					<note facs="#f021_z039" type="compositorial" xml:id="note_ea151d969381424192d24bdc896fde1c">Alexander</note>
				</p>
				<p>subse<metamark change="metadata#StE" facs="#f021_z038" function="line-end_hyphenation" place="inline" rend="bracket">bracket</metamark>quently fancying to himself some ideal<lb/> image of the man and his mind<add change="metadata#StBa" facs="#f021_z037" hand="metadata#HM" place="inline" rend="no_caret">.</add> And if<lb/> you rightly look for it<add change="metadata#StBa" facs="#f021_z036" hand="metadata#HM" place="inline" rend="no_caret">,</add> you will almost<lb/> always find that <add change="metadata#StC" facs="#f021_z035" hand="metadata#HM" place="inline" rend="no_caret">t</add>he <metamark change="metadata#StC" facs="#f021_z034" function="addition" place="inline" rend="caret">caret</metamark><add change="metadata#StB" facs="iiifmossesmanifest.json#f021_z000" hand="metadata#HM" place="above" rend="caret">author</add> himself has some<del change="metadata#StB" facs="iiifmossesmanifest.json#f021_z001" hand="metadata#HM" rend="single-stroke">how</del><add change="metadata#StB" facs="iiifmossesmanifest.json#f021_z002" hand="metadata#HM" place="above" rend="no_caret">where</add><lb/> furnished you with his own picture<add change="metadata#StBa" facs="#f021_z032" hand="metadata#HM" place="inspace" rend="no_caret">.</add> <metamark change="metadata#StB" facs="#f021_z031" function="space" place="inspace" rend="caret">caret?</metamark>For<lb/> poets (whether in prose or verse)<add change="metadata#StBa" facs="#f021_z030" hand="metadata#HM" place="inline" rend="no_caret">,</add> being painters<lb/> of Nature<add change="metadata#StBa" facs="#f021_z029" hand="metadata#HM" place="inline" rend="no_caret">,</add> are like their brethren of the pencil<add change="metadata#StBa" facs="#f021_z028" hand="metadata#HM" place="inline margin" rend="no_caret">,</add><lb/> <metamark change="metadata#StB" facs="#f021_z041" function="correction" place="margin left" rend="x">x</metamark>the true portrait-painters<add change="metadata#StBa" facs="#f021_z027" hand="metadata#HM" place="inline" rend="no_caret">,</add> <del change="metadata#StBa" facs="iiifmossesmanifest.json#f021_z003" hand="metadata#ESM" rend="single-stroke">will</del> <metamark change="metadata#StBa" facs="#f021_z026" function="insertion" place="below" rend="caret">caret</metamark><add change="metadata#StBa" facs="iiifmossesmanifest.json#f021_z004" hand="metadata#ESM" place="above" rend="caret">who</add>, in the multitude<lb/> of likenesses to be <del change="metadata#StC" facs="iiifmossesmanifest.json#f021_z005" hand="metadata#HM" rend="single-stroke">touched</del> <metamark change="metadata#StC" facs="#f021_z025" function="insertion" place="below inline above" rend="caret">caret with guiding line</metamark><add change="metadata#StC" facs="iiifmossesmanifest.json#f021_z006" hand="metadata#HM" place="above" rend="caret">sketched,</add> do not <del change="metadata#StC" facs="iiifmossesmanifest.json#f021_z007" hand="metadata#HM" rend="single-stroke">always</del> <metamark change="metadata#StC" facs="#f021_z024" function="insertion" place="below inline above" rend="caret">caret with guiding line</metamark><add change="metadata#StC" facs="iiifmossesmanifest.json#f021_z008" hand="metadata#HM" place="above" rend="caret">invariably</add> <lb/> omit their own<add change="metadata#StC" facs="#f021_z023" hand="metadata#HM" place="inspace" rend="no_caret">;<reg change="metadata#StE" facs="#f021_z033"> &amp; </reg>in all high instances, they paint them</add><lb/> <add change="metadata#StC" facs="iiifmossesmanifest.json#f021_z009" hand="metadata#HM" place="below" rend="no_caret">without any vanity, <del change="metadata#StC" facs="iiifmossesmanifest.json#f021_z010" hand="metadata#HM" rend="single-stroke">a both</del> though, at times, with a lurking something,</add><add change="metadata#StC" facs="iiifmossesmanifest.json#f021_z011" hand="metadata#HM" place="inspace margin" rend="no_caret">take several pages to properly define.</add><lb/></p>
				<quote change="metadata#readingNH" facs="#f021_z008" source="Mosses">
					<p><add change="metadata#StBa" facs="#f021_z022" hand="metadata#HM" place="inline" rend="no_caret"><metamark change="metadata#StBa" facs="#f021_z022" function="break" place="inline" rend="bracket">bracket</metamark></add>I submit it<add change="metadata#StBa" facs="#f021_z021" hand="metadata#HM" place="inline" rend="no_caret">,</add> then<add change="metadata#StBa" facs="#f021_z020" hand="metadata#HM" place="inline" rend="no_caret">,</add> to those best<lb/> acquainted with the man personally<add change="metadat#StBa" facs="#f021_z019" hand="metadata#HM" place="inline" rend="no_caret">,</add> whether<lb/> the following is not Nathaniel Hawthorne<add change="metadata#StBa" facs="#f021_z018" hand="metadata#HM" place="inspace" rend="no_caret">;--</add><lb/>and to himself<add change="metadata#StBa" facs="#f021_z017" hand="metadata#HM" place="inline" rend="no_caret">,</add> whether something involved in<lb/> it does not express the temper of this mind<add change="metadata#StBa" facs="#f021_z016" hand="metadata#HM" place="inline" rend="no_caret">,</add><lb/><add change="metadata#StBa" facs="#f021_z015" hand="metadata#HM" place="inspace margin" rend="no_caret">--</add>that lasting temper of all true, candid men<lb/><add change="metadata#StBa" facs="#f021_z014" hand="metadata#HM" place="inspace margin" rend="no_caret">--</add>a seeker<add change="metadata#StBa" facs="#f021_z013" hand="metadata#HM" place="inline" rend="no_caret">,</add> not a finder yet<add change="metadata#StBa" facs="#f021_z012" hand="metadata#HM" place="inspace" rend="no_caret">:--</add><lb/></p>
					<p>A man now entered, in neglected attire, with the<lb/> aspect of a thinker, but somewhat too rough-hewn and brawny for a scholar<add change="metadata#StBa" facs="#f021_z011" hand="metadata#HM" place="below" rend="no_caret">.</add><lb/> His face was full of sturdy vigor, with some finer and keener<lb/> attribute beneath<add change="metadata#StBa" facs="#f021_z010" hand="metadata#HM" place="inspace" rend="no_caret">;</add> though harsh at first, it was tempered with the glow<lb/> of a large, warm heart, which had force enough to heat his powerful<lb/> intellect through and through. He advanced to the Intelligencer, and<lb/> looked at him with a glance of such stern sincerity, that<lb/> perhaps few secrets were beyond its scope.</p>
					<p><lb/>"<reg change="metadata#StE" facs="#f021_z009">"I seek for Truth",</reg> said he."<lb/></p>
					<p>
						<add change="metadata#StBa" facs="#f021_z007" hand="metadata#HM" place="inspace" rend="no_caret">x x x x x x</add>
						<lb/>
					</p>
				</quote>
				<p>Twenty-four hours have elapsed since writing the<lb/> foregoing. I have just returned from the hay mow<add change="metadata#StBa" facs="#f021_z006" hand="metadata#HM" place="inline below" rend="no_caret">,</add><lb/> charged more and more with love and admiration of Hawthorne<add change="metadata#StBa" facs="#f021_z005" hand="metadata#HM" place="below" rend="no_caret">.</add><lb/> For I have just been gleaning through the <reg change="metadata#StE" facs="#f021_z004">m</reg>osses<add change="metadata#StBa" facs="#f021_z003" hand="metadata#HM" place="inspace" rend="no_caret">,</add><lb/> picking up many things here and there that had previously<lb/> escaped me<add change="metadata#StBa" facs="#f021_z002" hand="metadata#HM" place="inline" rend="no_caret">.</add> <metamark change="metadata#StC" facs="#f021_z001" function="addition" place="inline" rend="caret">caret with guiding line</metamark><add change="metadata#StC" facs="iiifmossesmanifest.json#f021_z012" hand="metadata#HM" place="above" rend="caret">And</add> I found that but to glean after this man<add change="metadata#StBa" facs="#f021_z000" hand="metadata#HM" place="inline" rend="no_caret">,</add></p>
			</div>
